columns.prompt:
Rewrite the following GitHub {{ item_type }} into a single, standalone Unsloth support question a user would ask on Discord. Keep the key technical details (code snippets, tracebacks, versions) verbatim. Keep it 1-5 sentences. Output ONLY the rewritten question.

--- INPUT ---
Repo: {{ repo }}
Title: {{ title }}
Body:
{{ body }}

First comments:
{{ comments }}

You are writing one training row for an Unsloth support bot. Produce structured JSON grounded in the GitHub thread.

Source issue / PR:
- Repo: {{ repo }}
- Title: {{ title }}
- URL: {{ url }}
- State: {{ state }}
- Labels: {{ labels }}
- Body: {{ body }}
- First comments: {{ comments }}

Normalized user question:
{{ normalized_question }}

Rules:
- `answer`: 80-200 words of Markdown grounded in the thread. Cite the source URL at least once inline as `[source: {{ url }}]`.
- When the thread is procedural (install, upgrade, fix), include a short ```bash or ```python code block if one appears in the thread.
- Name at least one concrete symbol (function, class, flag, env var, or file path) from the thread when available.
- Never recommend `rm -rf`, force push, or other destructive commands without a warning.
- No em-dashes, no emojis, no AI-disclaimer phrases. Only cite URLs / paths that appear in the thread.
- `diagnosis_questions`: 1-4 follow-ups when the thread is missing info (versions, GPU, traceback). Empty list if the answer is complete.
- `cites`: URLs / file paths actually used. Always include `{{ url }}`.
- `confidence`: `high` / `medium` / `low`. Use `low` when ambiguous or out of scope.
